    "narrative": "The offensive outlook for Ghost Ride the WHIP centers on the high-efficiency matchup against Wacha and the favorable hitting conditions for our middle-of-the-order bats. **Mickey Moniak** leads the squad with a 75.98 rating; despite facing the formidable Glasnow, **Mickey Moniak** gains significant equity from an aggressive +14% park factor and the opportunity to exploit a slow delivery, which is critical for our focus on SB efficiency. **Tyler Soderstrom** and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** are equally vital today; **Tyler Soderstrom** enjoys a massive +17% SP skill boost against Martin, while **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, even at the #7 spot, is a high-upside play against a weak 4.61 xERA, provided the 31% rain risk in the area doesn't force a delay or early exit.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today was the exclusion of **Alex Freeland**, who sits on the bench with a 58.63 score despite a robust +14% park factor. While **Alex Freeland** offers switch-hitting versatility, he was narrowly edged out by the superior power-projection floors of **Max Muncy** and **Seiya Suzuki**. Speaking of **Seiya Suzuki**, he remains a primary start thanks to a helpful wind-out scenario (+5%) against Senga. We are keeping a close watch on **Vinnie Pasquantino** and **Giancarlo Stanton** due to that 31% rain probability; should the weather turn, we have depth ready on the bench. **Corbin Carroll** remains our X-factor today, as his lineup status is pending, but his +8% order bonus and elite stolen base potential keep him firmly in the OF5 slot regardless of the rotation, provided he slots into the #2 hole as projected.",
